# Ensure the DOJ and DOE columns are in datetime format
df[''DOJ''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''DOJ''], errors=''coerce'')  # Convert DOJ (Date of Joining) to datetime
df[''DOE''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''DOE''], errors=''coerce'')  # Convert DOE (Date of Exit) to datetime
 
 
# Assuming today''s date to calculate tenure
today = pd.Timestamp.now()
 
# Create a new column for tenure in years
df[''Tenure_Years''] = (today - df[''DOJ'']).dt.days / 365
 
# Create the new classification column
def tenure_classification(tenure_years):
    if tenure_years < 1:
        return ''Early Tenure''
    elif tenure_years > 5:
        return ''High Tenure''
    else:
        return ''Others''
 
df[''Tenure''] = df[''Tenure_Years''].apply(tenure_classification)
 
def get_tenure_bucket(tenure_years):
    if tenure_years <= 0.5:
        return ''Upto 6 mo''
    elif 0.5 < tenure_years <= 1:
        return ''6M-1 Year''
    elif 1 < tenure_years <= 2:
        return ''1-2Y''
    elif 2 < tenure_years <= 5:
        return ''2-5Y''
    elif 5 < tenure_years <= 10:
        return ''5-10Y''
    elif 10 < tenure_years <= 15:
        return ''10-15Y''
    else:
        return ''15+ Y''
 
# Apply the tenure bucket function to create the ''Tenure Bucket'' column
df[''Tenure Bucket''] = df[''Tenure_Years''].apply(get_tenure_bucket)

def calculate_ytd_attrition(df, today, attr_columns):
    ytd_attrition = {}
   
    # Convert ''DOJ'' and ''DOE'' to datetime
    df[''DOJ''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''DOJ''], errors=''coerce'')
    df[''DOE''] = pd.to_datetime(df[''DOE''], errors=''coerce'')
 
    # Define the start of the year
    if df[''DOJ''].max() < pd.Timestamp(today.year - 1 , 4, 1):
        start_of_year = pd.Timestamp(df[''DOJ''].max().year - 1, 4, 1)
    else :
        start_of_year = pd.Timestamp(today.year - 1, 4, 1)

 
    # Filter the DataFrame for voluntary separations that occurred within the YTD period
    df_filtered = df[(df[''Working Status''] == ''Separated'') &
                     (df[''Exit Type''] == ''Voluntary'') &
                     (df[''DOE''] >= start_of_year) & (df[''DOE''] <= today)]
 
    # Group by the attributes (e.g., ''3G Grade Level'')
    for attr in attr_columns:
        attr_group = df_filtered.groupby(attr).size()
       
        # For each group (e.g., each ''3G Grade Level'')
        for group_name, vol_separations in attr_group.items():
            # Total voluntary separations for this group
            total_separations = vol_separations
           
            # Calculate the headcount at the beginning of the year
            headcount_start = df[(df[attr] == group_name) & (df[''DOJ''] <= start_of_year) &
                                 ((df[''DOE''].isna()) | (df[''DOE''] >= start_of_year))].shape[0]
           
            # Calculate the headcount as of today
            headcount_today = df[(df[attr] == group_name) & (df[''DOJ''] <= today) &
                                 ((df[''DOE''].isna()) | (df[''DOE''] >= today))].shape[0]
           
            # Calculate the average headcount
            average_headcount = (headcount_start + headcount_today) / 2
           
            if average_headcount > 0:
                attrition_rate = (total_separations / average_headcount) * 100
            else:
                attrition_rate = 0
 
            # Save attrition rate, separation count, average headcount, headcount start, and headcount today
            ytd_attrition[f"{attr}_{group_name}"] = {
                ''attrition_rate'': round(attrition_rate, 2),
                ''separations'': total_separations,
                ''average_headcount'': round(average_headcount, 0),
                ''headcount_start'': headcount_start,
                ''headcount_today'': headcount_today
            }
   
    return ytd_attrition

def wrap_text(text, max_length=30):  
    if isinstance(text, str):
        words = text.split()
        wrapped_text = ''''
        line = ''''
        for word in words:
            if len(line) + len(word) + 1 > max_length:
                wrapped_text += line.rstrip() + ''\n''
                line = word + '' ''
            else:

        wrapped_text += line.rstrip()
        return wrapped_text
    return str(text)
